article.headline: S. Illinois 84, Indianapolis University 69
article.story: CARBONDALE, Ill. -- Kevin Dillard's 16 points led five Southern Illinois players in double figures in an 84-69 victory over Indianapolis on Tuesday night. The Salukis (2-0) got 11 points each from Anthony Booker, Tony Freeman, Nick Evans and Carlton Fay. Evans had a game-high seven rebounds as the Salukis posted a 30-22 advantage on the boards. Dillard added 10 assists. Southern Illinois hit 54.9 percent on 28-of-51 shooting. Darius Adams came off the bench to score 21 points for the Division II Greyhounds (1-1). Ryan Sims added 15, Nate Blank 11 and DeWann Squires 10.
